race.comment: HUBBLE'S DRAGON (6) resumes today with three trials under his belt, winning the latest at Belmont over 1000m. Pike was on board for that effort and he remains with him today. The wide draw is a query, but he showed good ability in his debut campaign. Can knock this over back to Maiden company fresh. AWARDED GLORY (9) is on debut for Team Pearce and has shown some positive signs at the trials. CJP didn't partner the gelding, though his booking suggests that connections think he can fire on debut. Can play a leading role. GLORANARDO (10) is another debutant, this time for Rhys Radford. His latest trial was the most promising of the lot and the blinkers stick from that effort. Turner has been with him through his trials and he's not to be discounted. JACKPOT BINGO (1) has been solid at the trials and has claims first-up. HELIOS AMIGOS (2) was sound first-up at Bunbury and can improve.
